(42, 2, 10, 1, 12, 3, 3, 'all people', 'Blessing to All People', 'This connection highlights the theme of blessing for all families. Both passages emphasize that good news and blessings are intended for all people.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 10, 40, 14, 27, 27, NULL, 'Messages of Comfort and Joy', 'Both passages emphasize a message of reassurance, encouraging the recipients not to fear. The angel in Luke brings ''good tidings of great joy,'' while Jesus in Matthew reassures with ''be of good cheer.''', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 10, 42, 1, 30, 30, 'Fear not', 'Fear Not and Favor', 'Both passages emphasize the phrase ''Fear not,'' addressing individuals in moments of divine revelation. They highlight the reassurance provided by angels in the context of significant announcements.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 10, 42, 8, 1, 1, 'good tidings of great joy', 'Connection of Glad Tidings', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of ''glad tidings.'' In Luke 2:10, the angel announces good news to all people, while Luke 8:1 describes Jesus preaching the glad tidings of the kingdom of God.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 11, 23, 9, 6, 6, 'a Saviour, which is Christ the Lord', 'Connection of Birth and Titles', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of a child being born, highlighting his role as a savior and leader. The titles given in Isaiah reflect the nature of the Savior mentioned in Luke.', 'theme', 0.608, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 11, 40, 1, 21, 21, 'Saviour, which is Christ the Lord', 'Connection of Salvation in Birth', 'Both passages emphasize the role of Jesus as a Savior. Luke identifies Him as ''a Saviour,'' while Matthew states He ''shall save his people from their sins.''', 'theme', 0.524, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 11, 44, 2, 36, 36, 'Saviour, which is Christ the Lord', 'Connection of Jesus as Lord', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus as ''Lord'' and ''Christ''. The first identifies Jesus'' birth as the Savior, while the second declares Him as both Lord and Christ after His crucifixion.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 11, 56, 3, 4, 7, 'a Saviour', 'Connection of Saviour References', 'Both passages emphasize the role of Jesus as ''Saviour.'' Luke 2:11 announces His birth as the Saviour, while Titus 3:4-7 describes His saving work through mercy and grace.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 11, 40, 16, 16, 16, 'which is Christ', 'Connection of Christ''s Identity', 'This connection highlights the identity of Jesus as the Christ. In Luke 2:11, He is proclaimed as ''a Saviour, which is Christ,'' while Matthew 16:16 affirms Peter''s recognition of Him as ''the Christ, the Son of the living God.''', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 11, 42, 1, 43, 43, 'Lord', 'Connection of Lordship and Birth', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of the Lord. Luke 2:11 identifies Jesus as ''Saviour, which is Christ the Lord,'' while Luke 1:43 refers to Him as ''the mother of my Lord.'' This connection highlights the recognition of Jesus'' divine authority.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 11, 62, 5, 1, 1, 'Christ', 'Connection of Christ and Belief', 'Both passages emphasize the identity of Jesus as the Christ. Luke 2:11 introduces Jesus as the Saviour, while 1 John 5:1 highlights belief in Jesus as the Christ as a sign of being born of God.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 12, 23, 7, 14, 14, 'this shall be a sign unto you', 'Sign of the Birth', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine signs given at the birth of significant figures. Both passages emphasize a miraculous birth, with Isaiah mentioning a sign of a virgin conceiving and Luke detailing the sign of a babe in a manger.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 12, 23, 53, 1, 2, 'wrapped in swaddling clothes', 'Connection of Humility and Significance', 'This connection highlights the humble beginnings of Jesus as indicated by ''wrapped in swaddling clothes'' in Luke, paralleling Isaiah''s description of him as ''a tender plant'' with ''no form nor comeliness.'' Both passages emphasize the unexpected nature of the Messiah''s appearance.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 12, 19, 22, 6, 6, NULL, 'Connection of Humility and Reproach', 'This connection highlights the theme of humility found in both passages. The ''babe wrapped in swaddling clothes'' signifies lowliness, while ''a reproach of men'' emphasizes being despised, linking the two ideas of humble beginnings and societal rejection.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 12, 9, 2, 34, 34, 'this shall be a sign', 'Sign and Death Connection', 'This connection highlights the use of the phrase ''this shall be a sign'' in both passages. In Luke, the sign points to the humble birth of Jesus, while in 1 Samuel, it foretells the death of Eli''s sons, creating a contrast between life and death.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 12, 9, 10, 2, 7, 'sign unto you', 'Signs of Divine Guidance', 'This connection highlights the theme of signs given by God to guide individuals. In both passages, specific signs are provided to indicate God''s presence and purpose, with Luke mentioning a sign of the babe in a manger and 1 Samuel detailing signs for Saul''s journey.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 12, 12, 19, 29, 29, 'this shall be a sign unto you', 'Signs of Provision and Hope', 'This connection highlights the theme of signs given to indicate God''s provision. Both passages emphasize a sign that reveals a future promise of sustenance and care.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 12, 12, 20, 8, 8, 'sign unto you', 'Signs of Divine Intervention', 'This connection highlights the theme of signs given by God. Both passages emphasize the importance of signs as confirmations of divine action, with Luke presenting the sign of Jesus'' birth and 2 Kings discussing a sign of healing.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 13, 19, 103, 20, 21, 'heavenly host praising God', 'Angelic Praise and Service', 'This connection highlights the role of angels in praising God. Both passages emphasize the heavenly hosts and their obedience to God''s commands.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 13, 66, 5, 11, 11, 'a multitude of the heavenly host praising God', 'Heavenly Hosts in Praise', 'Both passages emphasize a multitude of angels praising God. In Luke, the heavenly host is seen praising at Jesus'' birth, while in Revelation, countless angels surround the throne in worship.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 13, 11, 22, 19, 19, 'heavenly host', 'Heavenly Hosts in Worship', 'This connection highlights the presence of the ''host'' in both passages, where the heavenly beings are depicted in worshipful roles. In Luke, the multitude praises God, while in 1 Kings, the host stands by the Lord, indicating their divine service.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 13, 19, 148, 2, 2, 'praising God', 'Angelic Praise Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of angels praising God. Luke 2:13 describes a multitude of angels praising, while Psalms 148:2 calls on all angels to praise Him.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 13, 27, 7, 10, 10, 'a multitude of the heavenly host', 'Heavenly Hosts and Ministering Beings', 'This connection highlights the presence of a multitude praising God in both passages. Luke describes a heavenly host, while Daniel mentions thousands ministering before God, emphasizing the theme of divine worship.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 13, 42, 15, 10, 10, 'praising God', 'Joy in the Presence of Angels', 'This connection highlights the theme of joy among angels in both passages. In Luke 2:13, the angels praise God, while Luke 15:10 emphasizes joy in the presence of angels over repentance.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 13, 58, 1, 14, 14, 'multitude of the heavenly host praising God', 'Angelic Ministry and Praise', 'This connection highlights the role of angels as ministering spirits in both passages. In Luke, the angels praise God, while in Hebrews, they are described as sent to minister to those who will inherit salvation.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 14, 45, 5, 1, 1, 'peace', 'Connection of Peace in Scripture', 'This connection highlights the theme of peace found in both passages. Luke 2:14 speaks of ''peace'' on earth, while Romans 5:1 emphasizes ''peace with God'' through faith.', 'theme', 0.475, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 14, 42, 19, 38, 38, NULL, 'Connection of Glory and Peace', 'Both passages emphasize the themes of glory and peace. The first passage speaks of ''glory to God in the highest'' and ''peace,'' while the second mentions ''peace in heaven'' and ''glory in the highest.'' This connection highlights the continuity of these themes in the narrative.', 'theme', 0.46099999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 14, 42, 1, 79, 79, 'peace', 'Connection of Peace and Guidance', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of peace. Luke 2:14 speaks of ''peace'' as a result of God''s glory, while Luke 1:79 mentions guiding feet ''into the way of peace.'' This connection highlights the importance of divine guidance leading to peace.', 'theme', 0.44699999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 14, 51, 1, 20, 20, 'peace', 'Peace and Reconciliation Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of peace. Luke 2:14 speaks of peace on earth, while Colossians 1:20 discusses making peace through the cross, highlighting the reconciliation of all things.', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 14, 23, 9, 6, 7, 'peace', 'Connection of Peace and Goodwill', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of peace, with Luke proclaiming ''peace'' and Isaiah referring to the ''Prince of Peace.'' This connection highlights the continuity of God''s promise for peace through the birth of the child.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
